    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <head>No. 239.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Cushing
                                    and McKenney</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Portland, Me.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 9</date>.
                                [Received April 9.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Having several fishing vessels ready for the Banks, we desire to know if
                            they can call at Canadian ports for men and be protected in so
                            doing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CUSHING &amp; McKENNEY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
